<ul local-id=3D"749b20c899ab">
<li local-id=3D"830d611fa62f">
<p local-id=3D"a7e1ff34354d">=E2=9D=8C Never allow <code>0.0.0.0/0</code> f=
or database ports.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"21af864945f6">
<p local-id=3D"d94fe0a491b6">=E2=9C=85 Allow access only from:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"784d132ddec9">
<li local-id=3D"da831fcc3c87">
<p local-id=3D"8cdeba665e4b">Specific EC2 Security Group (recommended)</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"2c2d8c1fe7e4">
<p local-id=3D"ba328c743b2c">Bastion host</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5da35451fdeb">
<p local-id=3D"abc3091c53ee">Corporate IP range</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"4f89f605bdd9">
<p local-id=3D"544848996578">=E2=9C=85 Keep database in private subnet (no =
public access)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9e32e76be87b">
<p local-id=3D"348a371c5f91">=E2=9C=85 Use IAM DB authentication where poss=
ible</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1e01fb9c310b">
<p local-id=3D"e0a734b18cb4">=E2=9C=85 Enable SSL/TLS connections</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b975a34fa915">
<p local-id=3D"3beb21c68b88">=E2=9C=85 Rotate credentials using AWS Secrets=
 Manager</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1f641ae65f7a"><strong>Golden Rule:</strong><br>
Database should never be publicly accessible unless absolutely required.</p=
>
